{
  "texts": [
    "To address this, numerous advanced 3D-CNN architectures have been proposed [32], [33], [150], [152].",
    "Recently, with the inspiration of Transformer [143] architectures in natural language processing, researchers have attempted to extend Vision Transformer (ViT) [89] for video modeling.",
    "Many works [4], [90], [91] propose different variants for spatiotemporal representation learning, and adapt to video action recognition task.",
    "However, learning favorable motion representations from original video clips remains a challenging task.",
    "To this end, various movement information have been previously examined to help extracting human action information from raw video, such as optical flow [85], motion vectors [115], [128], and pose data [19], [20]."
  ]
}